This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on Chinese conversations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural networks, which suggests it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves modeling and attention mechanisms, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with information extraction, which could also place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
